{
  "page": "Summer Tongue",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Summer Tongue</b> is the language used by the peoples of the <a href=\"/index.php/Summer_Islands\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Summer Islands\">Summer Islands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Some features of the language are: the lack of pronouns, the possibility of an imperfective aspectual marker, the probability of OSV sentence structure.<sup>[<i><a href=\"/index.php/Help:Manual_of_Style#References\" title=\"Help:Manual of Style\">citation needed</a></i>]</sup>\n</p><p>The \"xh\" in the Summer Islander's name <a href=\"/index.php/Jalabhar_Xho\" title=\"Jalabhar Xho\">Jalabhar Xho</a> may be a spelling for a <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/click_sound\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:click sound\">click sound</a>, as in the real-world Zulu and Khoisan languages.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Summer_Tongue&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_45\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 45\">Chapter 45</a>, Samwell V.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" class=